Nike Vomero 5 vs New Balance 2002r
Nike's Vomero 5 was originally released in 2011 and is currently on the Nike Vomero 16 model in 2023. 2022 saw a rise in the retro model bringing a lot of new fans into this year. Current prices on Nike Vomero 5 $160

Carve a new lane for yourself in the Zoom Vomero 5—your go-to for complexity, depth and now, easy styling. The richly-layered look includes textiles, real and synthetic leather and plastic accents that come together to make one of the coolest sneakers of the season. The reflective details put a little flash in your step, while the Black colorway makes them a certain win for any 'fit your wardrobe throws at you. It's a true tech meets low-key love story.

New Balance's 2002r originally came out in 2010 as a follow up to the New Balance 2001. The original 2002R had a $250 price tag. However the 2022 and current version of the 2002R has midsole of the 860V2 from 2012. Current Price of the New Balance 2002R are $140-$160

The New Balance 2002RD reintroduces a technical running favorite from the 2000s, outfitting the original design with modern performance upgrades. A suede and mesh upper construction is rendered with sleek curves and cutout segments for an updated take on a classic look. The performance of a Stability Web and N-ergy shock absorbing outsole stacked on an ABZORB midsole offer comfort and performance that can’t be pinned down with a date.

So why the comparison? They look similar and are both popular models currently!
Both models fit True to size IMO and can be bought in the description of the video if interested.
Nike Vomero 5 has more mesh, is softer on feet with Zoom air and cushlon underfoot and lighter as well. Has a more sporty look and feet IMO. 
New Balance 2002R has more suede and leather, more of a traditional cut and sew look with some mesh. 
The cushioning is firmer with the ABZORB midsole and Nrgy cushioning, however they are comfortable as well and have more support and traction. 

Which should you buy? Whichever you like more :) 
5 Similar things
Rubber and foam pod like heel cushion
Toe up rubber placement 
Largest branding on side of sneaker
Heel collar shape
Plastic tpu railes underneath for support

5 different things
Gusseted tongue on vomero
Side panel tpu on vomero, suede on 2002
Full rubber traction on 2002r
Vomero Softness on feet is better
Vomero is lighter
